{"type":"message","id":"5098218b","parentId":"7941b877","timestamp":"2026-03-30T18:57:41.375Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Good question. OpenClaw uses a \"default model\" (like gpt-4.1) when a request or session doesn’t explicitly specify a different model. If you want to use Gemini 2 (or any other model) for a particular reply, you need to:\n\n- Explicitly set the model when you make the request.\n- Or, change your agent/session’s default model to Gemini 2.\n\n**How to always use Gemini 2:**\n1. You can set the default model for your agent in your OpenClaw configuration:\n   - Edit your agent’s config (usually in your `.openclaw/agents/main/config.json` or via the UI).\n   - Set:\n     ```json\n     {\n       \"model\": \"gemini-2.0-pro\"\n     }\n     ```\n   - Or use `\"gemini-2.0-flash\"` if you prefer the faster version.\n\n2. Restart OpenClaw for the config changes to take effect.\n\n**Otherwise**, if you just ask questions without specifying, it will use the default (currently gpt-4.1).\n\nLet me know if you want help editing your config, or would like me to use Gemini for specific prompts!","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0134b14831f526be0069cac7a1657c819490067978caea5bc0\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-4.1","usage":{"input":176,"output":254,"cacheRead":12288,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12718,"cost":{"input":0.000352,"output":0.002032,"cacheRead":0.006144,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008528}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774897055613,"responseId":"resp_0134b14831f526be0069cac7a057b48194b33c5b06a2c6105c"}}
